1. Drag and Drop feature - Native HTML Draggable API

draggable attribute: Set draggable="true" on any HTML element (like a div, image, or paragraph) to make it draggable.

dragstart event: Add an event listener for dragstart to customize the drag behavior or to set drag data.


<img id="img1" draggable="true" ondragstart="event.dataTransfer.setData('text', event.target.id)">
<div id="dropzone" ondrop="onDrop(event)" ondragover="event.preventDefault()"></div>
<script>
function onDrop(event) {
  event.preventDefault();
  var data = event.dataTransfer.getData("text");
  event.target.appendChild(document.getElementById(data));
}
</script>

Common Draggable API Events:

dragstart: Begin dragging.
drag: While dragging.
dragend: When the drag operation is finished.
dragover: While dragging over a drop target.
drop: The draggable is released on a drop target.
